The paper deals with the synthesis of reactive systems using structured programs, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of automata and formal semantics also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal languages (cs.FL). The focus on reactive systems and their behavior suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE), while the use of algorithms and computational models suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
